snippet.title: Quake - Rapture (Part 3 of 4)
snippet.description:
Part three of me conquering Rapture. With three shamblers, two hell lords, and plenty of vores, this level is really tough. The Horn of Conjuring doesn't seem to work and some of ammo pickups are elevated, but nonetheless our Quake hero is always ready for a fight.

Rapture is a Quake episode by Tronyn and [Kona], released in September 2001. If you like this episode, be sure to check out [Kona]'s site at ethereal-hell.telefragged.com and visit Tronyn's Bazaar at tronyn.planetquake.gamespy.com.

Self Commentary:
I needed to bring out all my tricks just to stay ahead of the game. Because ogres can't aim up or down, there exists a spot where you can jump over their grenades; this was neccessary when moving left or right could have made the grenades ricochet. The knight's magic missles can always be jumped if the knight is within 5 degrees of your elevation. Shamblers always aim at your feet.
